text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia meisneri is a shrub belonging to the genus Acacia and the subgenus Phyllodineae. It is native to an area in the Wheatbelt region of Western Australia.The dense much-branched shrub typically grows to a height of 1.0 to 4.0 metres (3.3 to 13.1 ft). It blooms from November to February and produces yellow flowers.
